fields.body:
###Why is this conference in Portland, and who decided?

After four consecutive years on the West Coast (three in Portland and one in Mountain View), the sense of the community was that we needed a change of venue. Accordingly, the conference headed eastward for DjangoCon 2012 and 2013. Delegates to DjangoCon 2011, the last event held in Portland, had opportunity to voice their preference for future locations through a post-conference survey. Chicago was the overwhelming favorite.

fields.body:
###DJANGOCON IS FOR DEVELOPERS

Almost everyone who attends this conference develops Django, or uses Django to develop applications. Many do both. So this event is the place to meet and interact with Django developers.

DjangoCon is the place to find out straight from the horse's mouth what's coming down the pike. You will also discover lots of detail about an enormous range of applications different people are building with Django.

You can meet your friends from the Django community, socialize with Django core developers, and enjoy time in downtown Chicago with all it has to offer.

###IMPORTANT DATES



###CODE OF CONDUCT

All participants are expected to behave respectfully to each other. Very few appear to need this to be spelled out. For those who do, and for those who feel that they have not been respectfully treated, we have a [Code of Conduct](localhost:8000/about/conduct/)
